  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Previous works in social science (Cugno, 2020; Madera et al., 2009; Khan et al., 2021; Liu et al., 2009; Madera et al., 2019) have revealed the existence and dan-gers of gender biases in the language styles of professional documents.",
    "Such biases might lead to harmful gender differences in application success rate (Madera et al., 2009; Khan et al., 2021).",
    "For instance, Madera et al. (2009) observed that biases in gendered language in letters of recommendation result in a higher residency match rate for male applicants.",
    "These findings further emphasize the need to study gender biases in LLM-generated professional documents.",
    "We categorize major findings in previous literature into 3 types of gender biases in language styles of professional documents: biases in language professionalism, biases in language excellency, and biases in language agency."
  ],
